translated: Johansson, Gustaf Herder, pastor, G^s’säter, born September 26th, 1899 in Kungälv to the chaplain J. A. J. and Torborg Lundgren. Married in 1933 to Margareta Marberg. He graduated from secondary school in Gothenburg in 1922, theology degree in 1929, passed practical theology exam in 1932, and was ordained as a priest in Skara Diocese in 1931. He served in Fto, Finne Rödja, Sventorp, Ullervad, Odens-aker, Skövde, Fredsiberg, was the pastor in Österplana and Kestad before becoming the pastor in Gösisäter in 1946.
